2. Record investigation findings that classify root cause as workflow/state drift (revision without re-opening implementation path).
3. Emit a typed corrective action that creates an executable replacement task (and, if needed, abandons the stuck task with replacement linkage) so `do-task` can run again.
4. Finish by reporting `report_phase_outcome` with a concise complete summary.
